<!-- Downstream consumers:
  - Planner agent: reads phase goals/dependencies for plan creation. Needs: phase Goal, Provides, Depends on, Requirements, Success Criteria fields.
  - Build agent: reads current phase details for execution context. Needs: phase name, goal, planned plans, success criteria.
  - Status skill: reads progress table for completion tracking. Needs: Progress table with Milestone and Plans Complete columns.
  - Verifier agent: reads success criteria for phase verification. Needs: Success Criteria (2-5 observable behaviors) per phase.
  - check-plan-format.js (validateRoadmap): parses ## Milestone: sections and ### Phase NN: headings. Needs: exact heading format, **Goal:**, **Provides:**, **Depends on:** in each phase.
  - check-roadmap-sync.js: parses progress table rows against STATE.md phase status. Needs: progress table structure with Phase, Milestone, Plans Complete, Status, Completed columns.
  - Dashboard parseRoadmapMd: parses Phase Overview table. Needs: standard table format.
  Breaks if missing: Planner creates plans without dependency awareness; validators reject malformed roadmaps; dashboard shows empty roadmap.
-->
