## Evolution

This document evolves through the project lifecycle:
- **Created by:** `/pbr:new-project` during roadmap generation
- **Updated by:** `/pbr:execute-phase` as phases and plans complete (progress table, phase checklist)
- **Updated by:** `/pbr:discuss-phase` if scope changes require phase restructuring
- **Referenced by:** `/pbr:plan-phase` for phase scoping and dependency resolution

## Quality Criteria

A good ROADMAP.md satisfies:
- [ ] Every phase has **Goal:**, **Provides:**, and **Depends on:** fields
- [ ] Every phase has **Requirements:** with mapped REQ-IDs
- [ ] Every phase has **Success Criteria:** with 2-5 observable behaviors
- [ ] Phase numbers are sequential with no gaps (MUST start at 1, increment by 1 — no gap numbering like 10, 20, 30)
- [ ] Progress table row count matches phase count
- [ ] Progress table includes Milestone column for each phase
- [ ] Dependencies form a DAG (no circular dependencies)
- [ ] Phase Checklist items match Phase Details sections 1:1
- [ ] Requirement coverage line accounts for all Must-priority requirements
- [ ] Dependency graph is consistent with phase **Depends on:** declarations
- [ ] Completed milestones are collapsed in `<details>` blocks
